==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Placitum
<hw>Plac"i*tum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Placita</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL. See
<er>Placit</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A public court or assembly in
the Middle Ages, over which the sovereign president when a consultation
was held upon affairs of state.</def> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Old Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A court, or cause in
court.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A plea; a pleading; a judicial
proceeding; a suit.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plack</ent>⟦br⟧
